This paper discusses the issue of protecting intellectual property in deep learning models, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a new approach to embedding watermarks into DNNs, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the robustness of the proposed watermark against various model modifications, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
